							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/pasted-graphic-100x100.jpg" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/pasted-graphic.jpg 2x" alt="Nick Ripatrazone" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Nick Ripatrazone</h4>
												<p>Nick Ripatrazone is the culture editor at <em>Image Journal</em>, a contributing editor at <em>The Millions</em>, and a columnist at Lit Hub. He has written for <em>Rolling Stone</em>, <em>GQ</em>, <em>The Atlantic</em>, <em>The Paris Review</em>, and <em>Esquire</em>. He lives in Andover Township, New Jersey, with his wife and twin daughters. His latest book, <em>Longing for an Absent God</em>, is available from Fortress Press.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
